==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scapolite
<hw>Scap"o*lite</hw> <pr>(sk⟦acr⟧p"⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <?/ a staff, or L. <ets>scapus</ets> a stem, stalk +
<ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>scapolite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mon.)</fld>
<def>A grayish white mineral occurring in tetragonal crystals and in
cleavable masses. It is essentially a silicate of alumina and
soda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>scapolite group</xex> includes scapolite
proper, or wernerite, also meionite, dipyre, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapple</ent>⟦br⟧
